title: High Density of Commercial Bank Branches
description: San Marino boasts 122 commercial bank branches per 100,000 adults as of 2023, indicating a robust financial infrastructure.

title: Rapid Growth in Household Consumption Expenditure
description: In 2022, San Marino experienced a significant 15.56% growth in household consumption expenditure, showcasing a thriving consumer market.

title: Impressive Per Capita Consumption Growth
description: The per capita consumption expenditure in San Marino grew by 17.26% in 2022, reflecting increased individual spending power.

title: Substantial Investment in Health
description: In 2022, 29.51% of San Marino's general government expenditure was allocated to health, underscoring a strong commitment to public health.

title: High Male Survival Rate to Age 65
description: As of 2022, 93.95% of males in San Marino are expected to survive to age 65, indicating a high standard of living and healthcare.

title: Significant Male Population in Age Group 50-54
description: In 2023, 8.91% of San Marino's male population falls within the 50-54 age bracket, reflecting a mature demographic.

title: Notable Male Population in Age Group 55-59
description: As of 2023, 9.08% of the male population in San Marino is aged between 55-59, indicating a significant proportion of older adults.

title: Low Infant Mortality Rate
description: In 2023, San Marino reported an infant mortality rate of 1.4 per 1,000 live births, one of the lowest globally.

title: Minimal Under-Five Mortality
description: The under-five mortality rate in San Marino was 1.4 per 1,000 live births in 2023, showcasing excellent child healthcare.

title: Exceptional Pupil-Teacher Ratio in Primary Education
description: In 2018, San Marino had a pupil-teacher ratio of 6.93 in primary education, indicating personalized attention for students.

title: Low Probability of Child Mortality
description: The probability of dying among children aged 5-9 years was 0.2 per 1,000 in 2023, reflecting strong child health measures.

title: Minimal Rural Population
description: San Marino had a rural population of just 733 in 2023, indicating a predominantly urban society.

title: Limited Agricultural Contribution to GDP
description: In 2022, agriculture, forestry, and fishing contributed only 0.011% to San Marino's GDP, highlighting a service-oriented economy.

title: Low Percentage of Trained Female Teachers in Secondary Education
description: In 2023, only 2.84% of female teachers in secondary education were trained, indicating a potential area for improvement.
